    "body": "## Summary\n- validate tiled and im2col TMA descriptors before calling CUDA and report the violated constraints directly in the error message\n- print richer TMA debug context, including enum names, pointer alignment, raw strides, and the effective CUDA strides passed to `cuTensorMapEncodeTiled` / `cuTensorMapEncodeIm2col`\n- align host-side descriptor stack allocations to 64 bytes in both C and C++ host codegen paths\n- add regression coverage for runtime validation and generated host-source alignment\n\n## Example\nThe following dynamic-shape case now fails with a targeted runtime error instead of an opaque `Failed to initialize the TMA descriptor` message:\n\n```python\nimport torch\nfrom tilelang import language as T\nfrom testing.python.profiler.test_tilelang_profiler_dynamic_symbolic import matmul\n\nM = 128\nN = T.dynamic(\"n\")\nK = 128\nkernel = matmul(M, N, K, 64, 64, 32, dtype=T.float32, accum_dtype=T.float32)\n\nn_val = 1733\na = torch.randn(M, K, device=\"cuda\", dtype=torch.float32)\nb = torch.randn(K, n_val, device=\"cuda\", dtype=torch.float32)\nprint(b.stride(), b.stride(0) * b.element_size())  # (1733, 1), 6932 bytes\n\nkernel(a, b)\n```\n\nIt now reports the concrete constraint violation:\n\n```text\nInternalError\nInvalid TMA descriptor arguments for __tvm_tensormap_create_tiled:\n  [1] effective cuda globalStrides[0] (raw globalStride[1] = 6932) must be a multiple of 16 bytes\n...\nglobalStridesRaw [4, 6932]\ncudaGlobalStrides [6932]\n```\n\n## Validation\n- `pytest -q testing/python/runtime/test_tilelang_runtime_tma_validation.py`\n- `bash format.sh --files src/runtime/runtime.cc src/target/codegen_c_host.cc src/target/codegen_cpp.cc testing/python/runtime/test_tilelang_runtime_tma_validation.py`\n  - pre-commit checks passed\n  - local `clang-tidy` failed in this environment because system headers such as `stddef.h` were not resolvable\n\n\n<!-- This is an auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->\n\n## Summary by CodeRabbit\n\n* **Bug Fixes**\n  * Improved error messages when TensorMap descriptors fail validation, now displaying specific constraint violations instead of generic CUDA errors.\n\n* **Improvements**\n  * Enhanced memory alignment handling for CUDA TensorMap operations.\n  * Added detailed validation reporting for TensorMap arguments.\n\n* **Tests**\n  * Added test coverage for TensorMap validation and code generation alignment checks.\n\n<!-- end of auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->",
